---
import DocsLayout from '../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
---

<DocsLayout
    title="LSCSS FAQ"
    description="Frequently asked questions about Layered Semantic CSS."
>
    <section class="site-hero">
        <p class="eyebrow">FAQ</p>

        <h1>
            Frequently asked questions
        </h1>
    </section>

    <section class="content-block">
        <h2>
            Is LSCSS anti-utility?
        </h2>

        <p>
            No. Utilities exist, but they should remain small and intentional.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section class="content-block">
        <h2>
            Does LSCSS replace BEM?
        </h2>

        <p>
            LSCSS borrows ideas from BEM but focuses more heavily on layers,
            shallow selectors, and semantic readability.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section class="content-block">
        <h2>
            Does this work with frameworks?
        </h2>

        <p>
            Yes. The methodology focuses on CSS architecture rather than a
            specific framework.
        </p>
    </section>
</DocsLayout>
